es (Irina tries to control her tears). Why, then, should you want to go back, Arinushka? (Irina sobs in reply).’ Naturally, as would every fine player, mother improvised quite a bit, bless her soul. And moreover her voice—in young tuneful Russian!—is substituted for Le-nore’s corny brogue.”

Van had seen the picture and had liked it. An Irish girl, the infinitely graceful and melancholy Lenore Colline—

Oh! qui me rendra ma colline

Et le grand chêne and my colleen!



—harrowingl